searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint","doc":"Shared checkpoint vocabulary for replay and projection positions.","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint.html"},{"type":"type","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint.t/0","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint.advance/3","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint.html#advance/3"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint.new/1","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Checkpoint.html#new/1"},{"type":"module","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence","doc":"Struct and comparison helpers for fenced ownership.","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence.html"},{"type":"type","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence.t/0","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence.from_lease/1","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence.html#from_lease/1"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence.newer_than?/2","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Fence.html#newer_than?/2"},{"type":"module","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState","doc":"Shared handoff lifecycle vocabulary.","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.html"},{"type":"type","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.t/0","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.transition_allowed?/2","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.html#transition_allowed?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.valid?/1","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.html#valid?/1"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.values/0","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.HandoffState.html#values/0"},{"type":"module","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id","doc":"Helpers for replay-safe identifier construction.","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id.html"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id.build/2","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id.html#build/2"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id.random/1","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id.html#random/1"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id.valid?/1","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Id.html#valid?/1"},{"type":"module","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease","doc":"Struct and validation helpers for lease records.","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease.html"},{"type":"type","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease.t/0","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease.expired?/2","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease.html#expired?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease.new/1","doc":"","ref":"GroundPlane.Contracts.Lease.html#new/1"},{"type":"extras","title":"README","doc":"# GroundPlane\n\nGroundPlane is the shared lower infrastructure workspace for the nshkr platform\ncore.\n\nIt holds the reusable lower primitives that sit underneath `outer_brain`,\nCitadel, `jido_integration`, and `app_kit`.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Scope - README","doc":"- shared contracts and state vocabulary\n- Postgres transaction, outbox, inbox, and checkpoint helpers\n- generic projection publication helpers","ref":"readme.html#scope"},{"type":"extras","title":"Internal Libraries - README","doc":"- `ground_plane_contracts`\n- `ground_plane_postgres`\n- `ground_plane_projection`","ref":"readme.html#internal-libraries"},{"type":"extras","title":"Status - README","doc":"Workspace root established. The internal packages are intentionally small and\ngeneric.","ref":"readme.html#status"},{"type":"extras","title":"Development - README","doc":"The project targets Elixir `~> 1.19` and Erlang/OTP `28`.\n\n```bash\nmix ci\n```\n\nThe welded `ground_plane_contracts` artifact is tracked through the prepared\nbundle flow:\n\n```bash\nmix release.prepare\nmix release.track\nmix release.archive\n```\n\n`mix release.track` updates the orphan-backed\n`projection/ground_plane_contracts` branch so downstream repos can pin a real\ngenerated-source ref before any formal release boundary exists.","ref":"readme.html#development"},{"type":"extras","title":"Documentation - README","doc":"Workspace docs cover the overview, layout, contracts, Postgres helpers, and\nprojection helpers.","ref":"readme.html#documentation"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - README","doc":"MIT. Copyright (c) 2026 nshkrdotcom.","ref":"readme.html#license"},{"type":"extras","title":"Contracts","doc":"# Contracts\n\n`ground_plane_contracts` holds the lower shared contract surface.\n\nCurrent contract families:\n\n- ids\n- handoff states\n- leases\n- fences\n- checkpoints\n\nThe package is intentionally pure. It should remain reusable across:\n\n- `outer_brain`\n- `citadel`\n- `jido_integration`\n- `app_kit`\n\nIt must not depend on product truth or runtime-specific side effects.","ref":"contracts.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Overview","doc":"# Overview\n\nGroundPlane is the shared lower infrastructure layer for the platform core.\n\nIt exists to keep lower reusable primitives out of higher runtime repos.\n\nThe repo owns:\n\n- replay-safe ids\n- shared handoff-state vocabulary\n- lease and fence structs\n- checkpoint vocabulary\n- generic Postgres helper modules\n- generic projection publication helpers\n\nThe repo does not own:\n\n- semantic journals\n- policy truth\n- run and attempt truth\n- operator or governed-run semantics\n- product trust or review logic","ref":"overview.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Postgres Helpers","doc":"# Postgres Helpers\n\n`ground_plane_postgres` provides generic helpers for persistence patterns that\nmultiple repos will need.\n\nCurrent helper families:\n\n- transaction helpers\n- advisory-lock key helpers\n- outbox and inbox row helpers\n- checkpoint row helpers\n\nThese helpers are intentionally generic over the caller's schemas and tables.\nThey return or transform generic row maps and helper values instead of owning\nproduct semantics.","ref":"postgres_helpers.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Projection","doc":"# Projection\n\n`ground_plane_projection` provides generic projection publication helpers.\n\nThe package owns:\n\n- publication record building\n- generic payload shaping\n- adapter behavior for external sync surfaces\n\nThe package does not choose the primary sync product itself.\nIt stays adapter-shaped so higher repos can bind the chosen sync surface later\nwithout hard-coding that decision into the lower shared layer.\n\nThe workspace tracks the welded `ground_plane_contracts` artifact through the\nprepared bundle flow:\n\n```bash\nmix release.prepare\nmix release.track\nmix release.archive\n```\n\n`mix release.track` updates the orphan-backed\n`projection/ground_plane_contracts` branch so downstream repos can pin a real\ngenerated-source ref before any formal release boundary exists.","ref":"projection.html"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}